page.title: 15Ecology:Botany:Summer.
page.content: Beck Mill contains a wide variety of habitat which produces the following wild flowers in summer; Chamomile,Sorrel,Birdsfoot Trefoil, Horseshoe vetch,Comfrey,Cinquefoil, Silverweed,Hop Trefoil, White Campion Cornflower,Woody nightshade,Red clover Cow parsley,white clover,Common vetch, Wand wort,Stinging nettle,Rasberry, Blackberry,Cleavers,Poppy,Horse tail, Hemlock,Dock,Cranesbill, Yarrow, Plantain,Thistle,Hedge bedstraw,Tufted vetch,Melancholy thistle, Sweet briar, Honeysuckle, Foxglove,Rose bay willow herb,Great burnet,Ragwort, meadowsweet Autumn; St.Johns wort, Hedge bindweed Burdock, Red deadnettle, Harebell, Gorse(all year), Heather, Fat hen. The above are justthe common flowers identified around Beck Mill by Daniel Males and is by no means exhaustive.
